<comment type="function">
<text evidence="1 2">A global transcription factor. Activates transcription of the 9 following operons; yjjQ-bglJ, yjjP, acrEF, ybdO, yjcRQP, casABCDE12, rhsD-ybbC, fepE and gltF, in most cases it probably interferes with silencing by H-NS and activates transcription. Represses transcription of the 3 following operons; uxaCA, sdaCB and yjiY. H-NS repression of the bgl operon, leading to the ability to metabolize some beta-glucosides. It also directly activates the bgl operon. Activation is H-NS and BglJ-RcsB independent.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="induction">
<text evidence="1">Gene expression is repressed by H-NS, activated by itself. More highly expressed in minimal than rich medium, poorly expressed in exoponential growth, levels increase in stationary phase (at protein level).</text>
</comment>
<comment type="disruption phenotype">
<text evidence="3">Has no effect on leucine biosynthesis nor on bgl operon silencing.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="similarity">
<text>Contains 1 HTH lysR-type DNA-binding domain.</text>
</comment>
